<body>
    <h1>Get Occupancy</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <p local-id=3D"2ad017c6442e"><strong>Component type:</strong> Actio=
n</p>
<p local-id=3D"49b9dbd2c36c"><strong>Category:</strong> Spaces, Rates &amp;=
 Occupancy</p>
<h2 local-id=3D"94319950bf53" id=3D"GetOccupancy-Overview">Overview</h2>
<p local-id=3D"1f94eb3973e5">The <strong>Get Occupancy</strong> action retr=
ieves the occupancy percentage for your property on a specific date. It cal=
culates how many of your bookable spaces (rooms) are occupied relative to t=
he total available, returning a single percentage value. You can optionally=
 filter by one or more bookable services to get the occupancy for a specifi=
c subset of your property.</p>
<p local-id=3D"4ae32ec62175">This component is useful for building workflow=
s that react to occupancy levels =E2=80=94 for example, adjusting staffing =
when occupancy is high, sending alerts when occupancy drops below a thresho=
ld, or generating daily occupancy reports.</p>
<p local-id=3D"ecebb609d511">When the occupancy is successfully retrieved, =
the component outputs the date and the occupancy percentage on the <strong>=
out</strong> port, which can be used by subsequent steps in your workflow.<=
/p>
<hr local-id=3D"91d7768c-b087-4521-8180-49e153b25141">
<h2 local-id=3D"016390c5b64b" id=3D"GetOccupancy-InputFields">Input Fields<=
/h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"5350d910-5514-43c5-8e07-04e=
98e96bc68" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr data-local-id=3D"531535e1-4ead-4028-8c5e-5d31edeaa083">
<th data-local-id=3D"4eb71e58-5287-4f0d-80cc-66f4b16f4802" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"413c5f3cf403">Field</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"62af431f-6f60-47da-9eb4-4baae987d0c4" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"f095b55a864e">Required</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"bc8ece0c-7b2a-47b9-9e2e-cdd86291f63d" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"2313656fcdd7">Type</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"4400e76c-b410-4829-b959-ecff2cd786c9" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"c642432d7976">Description</p></th>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"520916d8-3017-48a2-8d35-fcff9571d580">
<td data-local-id=3D"aa5c5474-5fcf-411e-9bf5-aa4d26e25486" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"4d3c73a3b9e6"><strong>Date</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"a6b70b5d-4142-4832-ac67-551c1e4749c7" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"2d38d2e5cbcc"><strong>Required</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"d28a39ce-8d6c-4659-a518-a646561c65f1" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"330ddea19cc8">Date</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"1ace8904-bc80-4d03-9cfc-4b20b634cf0a" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"b227c67b2e40">The date to check occupancy for. Only the date=
 portion is used (time is ignored). Accepted format: <code>YYYY-MM-DD</code=
>. This can be set manually or populated dynamically from a previous step i=
n the workflow.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"0184ca00-d61c-456e-8d08-b6f9cae59d8e">
<td data-local-id=3D"78f33b51-ea7d-4026-9f24-9b1d135451de" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"d8e800839316"><strong>Bookable Services</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"821452f0-6e96-4261-b70a-5e131d67c670" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"6194828ab9f1"><strong>Optional</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"716559e3-8b80-47b2-98b9-9031b8e7f43c" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"b90a5dc5bed5">Multi-select dropdown</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"a6334577-3905-4c49-a728-03ca42170157" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"7ade5db4ce04">Select one or more bookable services to filter=
 the occupancy calculation. The dropdown is populated dynamically with the =
bookable services configured in your property. If no services are selected,=
 all bookable services are included in the calculation.</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"97fb800c90b1"><strong>Note:</strong> When no bookable servic=
es are selected, the occupancy percentage reflects the overall occupancy ac=
ross all bookable services in your property. If you select specific service=
s, only the spaces associated with those services are considered.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"b72af93d-5af9-4219-b375-5bc30d0f3246">
<h2 local-id=3D"ea1990dc4244" id=3D"GetOccupancy-OutputFields">Output Field=
s</h2>
<p local-id=3D"2a5275e7467f">When the occupancy is successfully retrieved, =
the following values are available on the <strong>out</strong> output port =
for use in subsequent workflow steps:</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"88fc3a30-5a43-4a71-a787-ba9=
9da5e8dec" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr data-local-id=3D"5057f8f5-f44b-41f7-b04e-94754b701a9f">
<th data-local-id=3D"d46c0ef9-83a4-4693-88d4-b307681ff9e9" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"9c2a7c1b573a">Field</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"a36e07fd-6217-4301-9111-70c64b8663db" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"0d1a55c7300d">Type</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"be086d6f-9ba8-4d4f-b4de-5495201444e0" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"bab40ceade4f">Description</p></th>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"84e92291-41a5-45ec-b95f-66b7bd0a8143">
<td data-local-id=3D"0ba8a051-8695-45d5-b738-85450b5c1d77" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"d927f1485d68"><strong>Date</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"0c4fed01-393d-4854-88f7-96c7eac0ec26" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"0dac67d1743b">Date</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"3776f714-9f3a-4b6d-96a3-3ce9d0c9696d" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"e65ddbb6d0e6">The date for which the occupancy was calculate=
d, in <code>YYYY-MM-DD</code> format.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"207b3046-1572-4103-a060-734f8f1b31c8">
<td data-local-id=3D"3551a1f6-440d-4c25-8eaa-0115e56bc5b4" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"2f565570ed99"><strong>Occupancy Percentage</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"ac6bfe67-6b52-4f09-976a-929917e8449c" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"2fc2ace7839a">Number</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"aa2d351b-537c-4655-9f32-3b973f1fb6d7" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"576e7f99f48c">The occupancy percentage for the specified dat=
e, expressed as a value between <code>0</code> and <code>100</code>, rounde=
d to two decimal places. For example, <code>75.50</code> means 75.50% of av=
ailable spaces are occupied.</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<hr local-id=3D"10118060-7e28-4ba5-bc1a-c206f3154bfa">
<h2 local-id=3D"9bb9c6023911" id=3D"GetOccupancy-HowItWorks">How It Works</=
h2>
<ol start=3D"1" local-id=3D"8f7d5e37-80f3-40bc-b1e4-401764266b26">
<li local-id=3D"da227811-7055-4c1b-9010-3b5af06b9dfd">
<p local-id=3D"4d7d81053102">The component receives the target date and opt=
ional bookable service filter from the previous step in the workflow (or fr=
om manually configured values).</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"cfae7504-3e89-41fa-8f77-1655d4be7d4c">
<p local-id=3D"d33f32f6be3b">The date is normalized to its date-only form (=
the time portion is stripped), and the system evaluates all activity within=
 that single calendar day.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"31db46ac-a019-4317-8c8b-db27ed2db5db">
<p local-id=3D"be618765768c">The system determines the <strong>total number=
 of occupiable spaces</strong> =E2=80=94 these are the rooms/spaces assigne=
d to the selected bookable services (or all bookable services if none are s=
elected) within your property.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"f27ab2ce-ba4d-4727-9408-4db1f162e53a">
<p local-id=3D"69cf2d0ab2b6">The system then determines which spaces are <s=
trong>occupied</strong> on the target date by looking at:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"771f3b41-9432-4932-b2e8-c1d016e74ee3">
<li local-id=3D"a8588c96-5652-4979-aea1-784bb24538e8">
<p local-id=3D"1a8321b6330d"><strong>Reservations</strong> =E2=80=94 Active=
 reservations (not processed or canceled) that overlap with the target date=
 and have an assigned space.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"5a8d210c-9375-496b-912f-d00f3b95a09f">
<p local-id=3D"24908f862ed8"><strong>Out-of-order blocks</strong> =E2=80=94=
 Resource blocks (e.g., maintenance, out-of-order) that overlap with the ta=
rget date.</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li local-id=3D"61ca6fbb-2298-401b-a871-93a6bb665ca1">
<p local-id=3D"76a29f05a160">For hierarchical space setups (e.g., a dorm be=
d inside a dorm room), if any space in a hierarchy is occupied, all related=
 parent and child spaces are also considered occupied.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"e1aae3d4-d31b-4059-8516-4d4a5792b91c">
<p local-id=3D"4fe3e45a72f3">The occupancy percentage is calculated as: <co=
de>(occupied spaces / total occupiable spaces) =C3=97 100</code>, rounded t=
o two decimal places.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"03cf317a-ed39-4efd-bb02-4a33bca9b26e">
<p local-id=3D"3155eb22d608">If there are no occupiable spaces (e.g., no se=
rvices configured), the occupancy percentage is <code>0</code>.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"23e112cb-69b2-459a-80ac-27ac20092987">
<p local-id=3D"6f26356c12f9">The result is sent to the <strong>out</strong>=
 output port.</p></li>
</ol>
<p local-id=3D"7df6d0bda3d4"><strong>Important:</strong> Out-of-order block=
s count as occupied spaces in the occupancy calculation. If a room is block=
ed for maintenance, it is treated as occupied for the purposes of this comp=
onent.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"880fd756-0d64-462e-b3b7-3543b4075195">
<h2 local-id=3D"900be53de7d4" id=3D"GetOccupancy-ExampleUseCases">Example U=
se Cases</h2>
<ul local-id=3D"0bdbfd64-edcb-4cc4-95c9-5935bb7567c8">
<li local-id=3D"3bccfd75-797c-4ce4-b28c-9e7adb911924">
<p local-id=3D"ccf2a41b0ce1"><strong>Daily occupancy report</strong> =E2=80=
=94 Schedule a workflow that runs every morning, retrieves today's occupanc=
y, and sends a summary notification to the operations team.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"0b25123a-ccb9-419a-9149-a3a7950ab4cd">
<p local-id=3D"862e93052f82"><strong>Low-occupancy alert</strong> =E2=80=94=
 Combine with a condition step to send an alert when occupancy drops below =
a certain threshold, allowing the revenue team to take action.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"22e234d6-afd0-4d4e-a7f7-944245ac07e3">
<p local-id=3D"08870237d182"><strong>High-occupancy staffing</strong> =E2=
=80=94 When occupancy exceeds a threshold (e.g., 90%), automatically create=
 tasks for additional housekeeping or front-desk staff.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"14686694-75db-433b-a0fc-83a32c1a3dce">
<p local-id=3D"1f51721d7fdb"><strong>Service-specific monitoring</strong> =
=E2=80=94 Track occupancy for a specific bookable service (e.g., only your =
hotel rooms, excluding parking spaces) to get a more targeted view.</p></li=
>
</ul>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
